Great post. I definitely agree that XSS is a severe security risk in this growing JS day and age. But it is also a relatively well known security issue vs say CSRF/XSRF (Cross-site Request Forgery). <br /><br />I do believe that proper coding should be where the solution lies, sanitizing any form of input so XSS is never possible as output.<br /><br />I would definitely recommend you bringing up your ideas to the mailing list. There are several people that use the mailing list and not the forums.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1763">Xdega</a> — Wed Jul 20, 2011 7:06 pm</p><hr />
